The Kuwaiti authorities have instructed that there will be no commercial flights into Kuwait after midnight on 13 March until further notice.
The British Embassy Kuwait has been working to find options for British nationals to leave Kuwait, if they wish to return to the UK.
Flights
Qatar Airways operates daily commercial flights from Kuwait to UK via Doha. Check the Qatar Airways website.
The Kuwaiti Foreign Ministry has advised that seats could be available on a limited number of special Kuwait Airways flights to London. You can contact the Kuwait Airways call centre on 171.
Further travel restrictions and flight suspensions, including of currently scheduled flights, may be introduced at short notice. For the latest updates you should monitor the Kuwait Directorate General of Civil Aviation on Twitter and the Kuwait News Agency.
You will need to pay for your return travel to the UK. If departure options are available but you cannot afford the travel costs and have exhausted all other options for getting funds, you may be eligible to apply for an emergency loan from the government. This is a last resort option and you would need to repay the loan when you are back in the UK. For more information, contact Corporate Travel Management (CTM). CTM are a commercial partner of the FCO and are authorised to administer such loans on behalf of the FCO.
Arrival in the UK
The National Travel Health Network and Centre (NaTHNaC) provides advice on how to stay safe as you travel by air.
When you arrive back in the UK, follow the guidance for when you return to the UK on steps you should take to protect yourself and others.
If you cannot leave Kuwait
If you cannot leave Kuwait at this time, see advice on staying in Kuwait during coronavirus.
Further information
See additional advice on making travel plans to return to the UK, or what to do if you cannot depart immediately.
